All Implemented Interfaces:
ICdmBase, IIdentifiableEntitiy, IParsable, ISourceable, IMediaDocumented, IMediaEntity, INomenclaturalReference, Serializable
public class BibtexReference
extends ReferenceBase
implements INomenclaturalReference

This class represents references which are structured according to the BibTeX format. The flat BibTeX format is an usual alternative to handle references (see BibTeX) Therefore this class might be used instead of StrictReferenceBase depending on the data to be imported in the CDM.

Version:
1.0
Author:
m.doering
See Also:

getCrossref

public BibtexReference getCrossref()
Returns the BibTeX reference this BibTeX reference belongs to (for instance a BibTeX reference with the entry type "INBOOK" belongs to another BibTeX reference with the entry type "BOOK").
The returned "crossref" attribute corresponds to the "inBook" and "inProceedings" attributes of BookSection and of InProceedings.

Returns:
the BibTeX reference containing this BibTeX reference

getNumber

public String getNumber()
Returns the string representing, if applicable, either the number of this BibTeX reference if it is a "TECHREPORT" (report) or of the journal in which this BibTeX reference was published if it is an "ARTICLE". Most publications have a "volume", but no "number".
In this case the returned string is included in the "title" attribute of StrictReferenceBase.

Returns:
the string identifying the number for this BibTeX reference (article or technical report)

generateTitle

public String generateTitle()
Generates, according to the default cache strategy assigned to this BibTeX reference, a string that identifies this BibTeX reference and returns it. This string may be stored in the inherited titleCache attribute.
This method overrides the generic and inherited generateTitle method from ReferenceBase.

Specified by:
generateTitle in interface IIdentifiableEntitiy
Overrides:
generateTitle in class ReferenceBase
Returns:
the string identifying this BibTeX reference
